\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \f1\b\fs18 Board and pieces\plain\f1\fs18
\par
\pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 The board supplies the playing squares. Each square is empty or contains one piece.
\par
\pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 On a monochrome monitor, red pieces are shown as white pieces and blue pieces are shown as black pieces.
\par
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \f1\b\fs18 Board and pieces\plain\f1\fs18
\par
\pard\sb35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 The board is an eight-by-eight square grid.
\par
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \f1\b\fs18 pieces\plain\f1\fs18
\par
\pard\sb35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 Pieces show which side controls a square.
\par
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \f1\b\fs18 empty square\plain\f1\fs18
\par
\pard\sb35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 An empty square can be used only if the move is legal.
\par
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \f1\b\fs18 Related Topics\plain\f1\fs18
