{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} POP_OUTFLANK}
\pard\sb45\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 To outflank means to place a piece so that one or more opposing pieces are between the new piece and another piece of your color.
\par
\page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} POP_MULTI_DIRECTION}
\pard\sb45\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs18 Multiple directions means that the same move outflanks pieces along more than one horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line.
\par
